505. testudine : the “ tortoise” was the covering formed by a body of soldiers locking their shields together above them, and so ap- proaching the enemy’s wall to fire or undermine it. An ancient camp was surrounded by four ramparts or walls (si-alla) formed of the earth dug from the ditch (fossa) on the outer side. The actual walls or palisades, with their towers, etc, surmounted the vallum. C . V. 524.
